IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: OPERATION OF A CONTINUING CARE RETIREMENT COMMUNITY TO PROVIDE HOUSING AND SERVICES TO RESIDENTS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF LIFE CARE PONTE VEDRA, INC. IS TO PROVIDE FOR THE HOUSING, PHYSICAL, EMOTIONAL, RECREATIONAL, SOCIAL, RELIGIOUS, HEALTH CARE AND FINANCIAL SECURITY NEEDS OF THE ELDERLY THROUGH THE OPERATION OF A CONTINUING CARE RETIREMENT COMMUNITY KNOWN AS VICAR'S LANDING.
IRS990.Desc: THE RETIREMENT COMMUNITY CONSISTS OF 227 INDEPENDENT RESIDENTIAL UNITS, 38 ASSISTED LIVING UNITS, AND A 60-BED SKILLED NURSING CENTER. THE ORGANIZATION OPERATES UNDER THE "CONTINUING CARE" CONCEPT IN WHICH RESIDENTS ENTER INTO AN OCCUPANCY AGREEMENT, WHICH REQUIRES PAYMENT OF A ONE-TIME ENTRANCE FEE AND A MONTHLY SERVICE FEE. GENERALLY, THESE PAYMENTS ENTITLE RESIDENTS TO THE USE AND PRIVILEGE OF VICAR'S LANDING FOR LIFE, INCLUDING CERTAIN NURSING SERVICES IN THE ORGANIZATION'S SKILLED NURSING FACILITY.

GRANTS ARE GENERALY MADE ONLY TO ORGANIZATIONS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER 501(C)(3) AND RESIDENTS OF THE FILING ORGANIZATION'S CONTINUING CARE RETIREMENT COMMUNITY. ACCORDINGLY, THE FILING ORGANIZATION HAS NOT ESTABLISHED SPECIFIC PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS IN THE UNITED STATES AS THE FILING ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE A GRANT MAKING PROGRAM THAT WOULD NECESSITATE SUCH PROCEDURES.

THE FILING ORGANIZATION'S OFFICERS ARE COMPENSATED BY A RELATED 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATION, LCPS MANAGEMENT, INC. THE FOLLOWING METHODS ARE UTILIZED BY LCPS MANAGEMENT, INC. SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE K, ROW A ENTITY 1, PART I(F)
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PURPOSE OF SERIES 2016 BONDS: IN NOVEMBER 2016, THE ST. JOHNS COUNTY INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY ISSUED ON BEHALF OF THE ORGANIZATION $15,725,000 HEALTH CARE REVENUE AND REVENUE REFUNDING BONDS (THE "SERIES 2016 BONDS") TO REFUND THE SERIES 2007 BONDS, PAY FOR CERTAIN CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS, AND PAY CERTAIN COSTS OF ISSUING THE SERIES 2016 BONDS. THE SERIES 2016 BONDS ARE COLLATERALIZED BY ASSETS IN TRUST, A MORTGAGE ON THE PROPERTY AND EQUIPMENT, AND GROSS REVENUES OF THE ORGANIZATION.

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION RELATED TO BOND ISSUANCE: ST. JOHNS COUNTY INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY REVENUE REFUNDING BONDS, SERIES 2016, PRINCIPAL AND INTEREST PAYMENTS ON THE SERIES 2016 BONDS ARE PAYABLE MONTHLY THROUGH MATURITY IN FEBRUARY 2037. THE SERIES 2016 BONDS HAVE AN ANNUAL VARIABLE INTEREST RATE EQUAL TO THE SUM OF 65% OF LIBOR PLUS 1.23% (1.6875% AT DECEMBER 31, 2016), WITH A TENDER OF OUTSTANDING PRINCIPAL AND ACCRUED INTEREST EXERCISABLE BY THE REGISTERED OWNER IN FEBRUARY 2027. THE ORGANIZATION ENTERED INTO A VARIABLE-TO-FIXED INTEREST RATE SWAP AGREEMENT TO EFFECTIVELY FIX THE ANNUAL INTEREST RATE ON THE SERIES 2016 BONDS AT 2.76%.
